'Tis near the Hour appointed, and that's the Shop we meet at;
the Mistress of it, Courtine, is a hearty Well-wisher to the Mathematicks,
and her Influence, I hope, may have no ill Effect o're my Adventure.

Would the Lady of my Motion would make haste, and be punctual;
the Wheels of my Nature move so fast else, that the Weight will
be down before she comes.

IS not this Living now? Who that knew the Sweets of Liberty,
the uncontroll'd Delights the Free-man tastes of, Lord of his,
own Hours, King of his own Pleasures, just as Nature meant him first;

The Main was Seven, and the Chance Four; I had just Thirty
pound upon it, and my last Stake: The Caster threw, nothing came of it;
I chang'd his Dice; he threw again, to as little purpose as before.

Your faux Braves always put on a shew of more Courage than ordinary;
as your beggarly half-Gentlemen always wear tawdry finer Cloaths
than their Fortune will afford 'em.

Sweet-heart, pray oblige me so far to shew me the way to the Gardens;
I come to pay a Visit to Madam Porcia, and am informed she's gone there
for the Air.—A very handsom Youth—

Be ready then, all ye propitious Powers, that smile on faithful Love;
Wait, like kind Angels, on him; Establish Conquest in his able Hand, and
Kindness in his Heart. Oh, Sylvia▪

Very well, Sir, I thank you, if I were but well off from this place;
I fear the man I had to deal withall is fallen, for I left him stagg'ring. Security
were best for us all, Sir.
